{"pattern":{"summary":"Fold llvm.ldexp when its exponent is a zero-extension of a 1-bit scalar or vector boolean into a select of {1.0, 2.0} followed by fmul.","match":{"intrinsic":"llvm.ldexp.*","operands":{"src":"floating-point scalar or vector","exp":"zext of i1 or vector of i1 to the ldexp exponent integer type"}},"preconditions":["The exponent operand is exactly a zext from a 1-bit integer source type.","Applies to scalar and fixed/scalable vector forms lane-wise.","The floating source/result type is any supported scalar or vector FP type accepted by llvm.ldexp.","Do not apply if the zext source element width is greater than 1."],"rewrite":{"description":"Since zext(i1) is only 0 or 1, ldexp(x, zext(i1)) == x * (zext(i1) ? 2.0 : 1.0). Replace the intrinsic with a select producing FP constants 2.0/1.0 in the result type, then multiply the source by that select.","pseudocode":["%c = select %bool, FP(2.0), FP(1.0)","%r = fmul %src, %c"],"notes":["Create FP constants in the exact scalar/vector result type.","Preserve fast-math flags from the original intrinsic call on the created fmul.","For vectors, build vector splat constants and a vector select."]},"why_correct":["If b is i1, then zext(b) ∈ {0,1}.","ldexp(x,0) = x.","ldexp(x,1) = x*2.","Therefore ldexp(x,zext(b)) = select b, x*2, x, equivalently x * select b, 2.0, 1.0."],"implementation_hint":{"instcombine_match":"match exponent as m_ZExt(m_Value(ExtSrc)) and require ExtSrc type scalar size == 1","builder_shape":["SelectInst::Create(ExtSrc, ConstantFP(2.0 in result type), ConstantFP(1.0 in result type))","BinaryOperator::CreateFMulFMF(Src, Select, II)"]}},"testcases":[{"name":"scalar_f32_basic","ir":"declare float @llvm.ldexp.f32.i32(float, i32)

